# WDBX-AI Project Architecture

## Core Structure
This is a **modular vector database** built in Zig with AI integration capabilities.

### Main Entry Points
- [src/main.zig](mdc:src/main.zig) - Primary entry point
- [src/main_refactored.zig](mdc:src/main_refactored.zig) - Refactored implementation
- [src/root.zig](mdc:src/root.zig) - Root module exports

### Core Modules
- [src/core/](mdc:src/core/) - Core utilities and system initialization
- [src/database/](mdc:src/database/) - Vector database implementation
- [src/simd/](mdc:src/simd/) - SIMD-optimized vector operations
- [src/ai/](mdc:src/ai/) - AI and machine learning capabilities
- [src/wdbx/](mdc:src/wdbx/) - Unified WDBX interface

### API Layer
- [src/api/](mdc:src/api/) - API implementations (CLI, HTTP, etc.)
- [src/plugins/](mdc:src/plugins/) - Extensible plugin system
- [src/utils/](mdc:src/utils/) - Common utilities and error handling

## Key Features
- **High Performance**: SIMD-accelerated operations with 2-4x speedup
- **Enterprise Ready**: Production features with monitoring and health checks
- **AI Integration**: Built-in neural networks and embedding generation
- **Scalable**: Handles millions of vectors with efficient indexing
- **Modular**: Clean separation of concerns with well-defined interfaces

